description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What’s special about this opportunity?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen to join the multidisciplinary specialist Neuro Rehab Team at West Berkshire Community Hospital. The dedicated Neuro Rehabilitation beds are for patients who require in-patient rehabilitation following an admission from the acute in a community hospital setting and support with planning their transition home and for some community admissions for specialist assessment and treatment. The role gives you flexibility in the delivery of the rehab for your patients during that important transition home and their continuation of meaningful activities. The unit also holds beds for rehabilitation and end of life/ palliative symptom management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role involves:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;direct patient contact to provide specialist assessment and rehabilitation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;discharge planning, integration into the community &amp; onward referrals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;cognitive &amp; capacity assessments to support patient’s involvement in the next stage of their rehabilitation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;joint working with the other disciplines from Physiotherapy, Speech and Language therapy and Psychology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handing over rehabilitation programmes to the highly skilled &amp; experienced therapy assistants in the team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Berkshire Healthcare Foundation Trust can provide you with a dynamic, people-centred environment, where you will be empowered to innovate, engage creatively and autonomously with patience and compassion to motivate and provide exceptional clinical care to patients in their rehabilitation, helping them to gain independence, through a culture of nurture and inspiration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We value our employees and put people first. We will provide you with an excellent working environment that has been recognised as an ‘Outstanding’ rating.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working in a passionate team, you will have access to our Trust-wide Learning and Development programme and be supported in your career and personal growth with opportunities to be actively involved in training courses, clinical and service development, and peer review, to help you build your Continuing Professional Development portfolio, extend your skills and ensure that you excel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are pioneers in compassionate leadership and Quality Improvement, which is about creating a culture where everyone has a voice and where service users and staff collaborate to have a direct impact on the things that matter most.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is an exciting opening to a person interested in joining a dynamic rehabilitation team who put the patient at the forefront of what they do. A team player with experience working with patients with Neurological conditions is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you enjoy working with a wide range of patients with various neurological conditions, show understanding and empathy, then this role is for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the role will include the transition home/ to supported living as part of their rehab it is essential that you have access to a car and be able to use it for work purposes and are flexible to travel between sites if necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your energy and drive will be rewarded with the support of an enthusiastic team that strives to ensure that the Trust is a sincere and compassionate place to work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The unit is based in a very pleasant working environment with an excellent canteen and therapy garden.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What’s next?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you share our passion for people and the dedication to excel, we’d love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are happy to answer any questions that you may have. Please don’t hesitate to contact Service Manager for Neuro Rehabilitation Lisa Ellis on 07771344281 or 01635 273303. Alternatively you can contact Lisa.Ellis@berkshire.nhs.uk . If you would like to come and visit the unit prior to application please contact Lisa.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to a competitive salary, as a valued member of our team, you will receive generous annual leave, have access to our salary car scheme, support with childcare and as a respected member of the NHS, discounts from high street retailers and restaurants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLisa EllisJob titleService Manager for Neuro RehabilitationEmail addressLisa.Ellis@berkshire.nhs.ukTelephone number07771344281&lt;/p&gt;
